About Business Analytics: Business analytics is the process of collating, sorting, processing, and studying business data, and using statistical models and iterative methodologies to transform data into business insights.

The goal of business analytics is to determine which datasets are useful and how they can be leveraged to solve problems and increase efficiency, productivity, and revenue.

 

 

 

Topics to be covered:

 

 Introduction to Business Analytics

 Different Type of Business Analytics

• Descriptive Analytics – Analysis what is happening and what happened in Business

• Diagnostic Analytics – Analysis how and why happened

• Predictive Analytics – Predict what will happen

 • Prescriptive Analytics – How to overcome from problem

Introduction to Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning

 • Supervised Learning

• Unsupervised Learning Components of Business Analytics

• Data Aggregation

• Data Mining

• Association and Sequence Identification

• Text Mining

• Forecasting

 • Optimization

• Data Visualization

Different tools

Careers in Business Analytics

Regression Analysis Case Study – Implementation





Duration: 23 to 24 July 2022 (2 Days  5 PM to 8.30 PM)  




Course Fee Rs. 2500

12/13/22, 09:37 - Rinku Raphy: 2. Case Study - Several Topics. 

This is one of my favorite "plan B" activities in my class (when I can't find something a little more engaging). I locate a case study that is relevant to my topic and customize it to meet the needs of the class. I start by having the students individually read the case study. Then as a group, I have them answer questions related to the topic that I have prepared in advance. You can also add additional questions from the book test bank to the case study to make it more challenging. You can find case studies on any topic - my favorite topics include ethics and leadership.
12/13/22, 09:40 - Rinku Raphy: Self Assessments - Several Topics.

Self assessments are a great way to engage the student by having them evaluate their own perspectives or skills in a topic area. For example, using Fiedlers Least Preferred Coworker scale to identify what type of leader they are. Or having them answer questions related to diversity to help them assess hidden biases they may have - I found a great set of questions here for that purpose -(Link). I then read back the answers and most students are very surprised by the answer. We then compare scores with each other, discuss the results - surprises, etc.

Hair Growth Oil எப்படி பயன்படுத்த வேண்டும்?.

தினமும் இரவு உறங்க செல்வதற்கு முன் தேய்த்துக்கொள்ளலாம்.
அல்லது காலை குளிப்பதற்கு ஒரு மணி நேரத்திற்கு முன் தேய்த்து கொள்ளலாம்.

தினமும் தலைக்கு குளிக்க வேண்டுமா?. தலைமுடியை கழுவ வேண்டுமா??

நீங்கள் வாரத்திற்கு இரண்டு முறை அல்லது ஒரு முறை தலைக்கு குளிப்பவராக இருந்தலும் தினமும் Hair Growth Oil தேய்க்க வேண்டும்.
தினமும் தலைமுடியை கழுவா விட்டாலும் கட்டாயம் தேய்த்துக்கொள்ள வேண்டும்..

3) எவ்வளவு அளவு தேய்க்க வேண்டும்..?.

நீங்கள் தேங்காய் எண்ணெய் பயன்படுத்தும் அளவிலே தேய்த்துக்கொள்ள வேண்டும்.

4) ஷாம்பூ/சீயக்காய் தினமும் பயன்படுத்தலாமா?..

தினமும் தலைக்கு ஷாம்பூ பயன்படுத்த வேண்டாம். வாரம் ஒரு முறை அல்லது இரண்டு முறை ஷாம்பூ பயன்படுத்திக்கொள்ளுங்கள்.

FAQ

Q1. How to use Vanga Annachi Hair Growth Oil?

A1. It can be applied daily night before you hit the bed or daily morning one hour before taking your routine bath.

Q2. Should I apply Vanga Annachi Hair Growth Oil even if I take Head bath only twice a week?

A2. Even if you are taking Head bath once a week, Vanga Annachi Hair Growth Oil should be applied daily for better results.

Q3. How much Vanga Annachi Hair Growth Oil should I apply?

A3. The same amount as normal Coconut Oil.

Q4. Can I use Shampoo/Sihaikaai ?

A4. Daily usage of Shampoo shall be avoided. It can be used once or twice if needed.

7/29/23, 10:03 - 💝Jo💝: <Media omitted>
7/29/23, 11:03 - 💝Jo💝: Hi All

Yesterday I attended a session organized by Apollo Hospitals on Wellness.  There were panel of doctors specialized in Liver, Radiology, General Medicine, Infectious Disease & Adult Vaccination, Neurology, Cardiology, Diet & Nutrition and Ortho.

While the panel discussion was emphasizing on several issues such as mobile usage, importance of diet and what is healthy eating etc, some of key takeaways that I wish to share to the team are as below:
a.	No excuse for Exercise.  Muscles and Bones need some flexing.  Food is not the only feed for Organs.  Our exercise and activities will keep our organs engaged and make them work happily for us.  One has to know the limit of exercise.  
 
b.	While exercising / jogging keep a watch on the Heart Rate.  We should give a pause to the activity when our heart rate crosses a limit.  Generally the limit is 220 minus our age (if someone is 40 years then the max heart rate can be 180).  Ideal is to restrict it at 120 to 130 max and take a pause.

c.	Ergonomics is so important  learn to keep the back erect at all times.  Keep the neck straight.  People bend down while seeing mobile which will have serious impact when we grow old.

d.	While Alcohol is bad for Liver – people tend to ignore Fatty Liver esp. Non-Alcoholic Fatty Liver.  Lifestyle changes alone will help in such conditions.  Be careful of what you eat and what you do.  Fatty Liver will lead to Liver Cirrhosis and hence we need to be watchful.

e.	Don’t over eat.  Stomach will accept extra food without much hesitation.  Its for us to decide base on the caloric index and our physical activity.  

f.	12 hours fasting is very important.  Have your food by 8.00 p.m. and next day breakfast should be by 8.00 a.m.  This will help in balancing our body.

g.	Any condition that is more than 2 weeks, consult a doctor without fail

h.	Headache is not an illness or disease.  It is an indication of some issue within the body.  Some less function or malfunction will mostly trigger in headache viz. poor gut health, nerve weakness etc.

i.	Avoid mobile phones in the bedside.  Not because of radiation but because of temptation to see.  In dark, it affects the eyes and brain.  It alters our sleep pattern thereby resulting in malfunctioning of our organs.  Sleeping 6-8 hours is mandatory and such disturbances will impact our health heavily.

j.	Spend more time with elders.  Take time and talk to them.  For geriatric more than medicines the human touch and time spent will make them feel better.  

There were few more points but I felt these simple ones are more important.

One input of Hepatitis B – If you find anybody a Passive Carrier, then it is better others close to them take appropriate vaccines.  Passive Carrier can spread it to others easily.  Also, passive carriers may become active carriers and may have issues w.r.t their health.  Its more dangerous.

3/7/25, 15:50 - Rinku Raphy: Tasty & Easy Bread Dates Pudding Recipe | Simple & Delicious Dessert

Looking for a quick and delicious dessert? This Bread Dates Pudding is super easy to make and absolutely tasty! With simple ingredients like bread, dates, and caramel, this pudding is perfect for any occasion.

Ingredients:
✅ Bread slices
✅ Dates
✅ Milk
✅ Sugar
✅ Eggs
✅ Vanilla essence( if necessary)

Steps:
1️⃣ Prepare the caramel base.
2️⃣ Mix the ingredients and pour over the caramel.
3️⃣ Steam or bake until set.
4️⃣ Enjoy your rich and flavorful pudding!

Try this easy dessert and let us know how it turns out in the comments!
